s:2873:"<h3 style="margin:0cm 0cm 15pt;">Regulatory Training</h3><p>Regulatory Training is located at Kensington and sits within the Regional &amp; Fire Management Executive, Regional &amp; Fire Management Services Division. It is responsible for the management of the Department's Authorised Officers, inclusive of training and application approval. In order to become an Authorised Officer (AO), a person must first make contact with the <a href="mailto:regulatory.training@dpaw.wa.gov.au">Regulatory Training Coordinator</a>. Good cause must be demonstrated as to why a person requires authority, which in most instances will be closely associated to their role in the Department.<br /></p><p><br /></p><div class="editor-indent" style="margin-left:30px;"><p style="text-align:center;"><img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/reg_train_banner_refresher.jpg" alt="Regulatory Training" width="914" height="150" style="vertical-align:middle;margin:0 .5em;" class="img-responsive" /></p></div><p><br /></p>

<p>You will need to make contact with Regulatory Training if you wish to become any of the following:
</p><ul><li><b>CALM Officer</b></li>
<li><b>Forest Officer</b></li>
<li><b>Ranger</b></li>
<li><b>Wildlife Officer</b></li><li><b>Inspector</b></li></ul><p></p>
<p>These also include powers under the <a href="http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_106_homepage.html">Bush Fires Act 1954</a>.
</p><p><br /></p><p>Additionally, you may wish to inquire about cross authorisation under legislation managed by other agencies.  Whatever your authority needs are, you will need to first make contact with  <a href="mailto:regulatory.training@dpaw.wa.gov.au">Regulatory Training Coordinator</a>.</p>

<p>Once an expression of interest has been accepted, the applicant will then be invited to participate in the relevant and required training. Successful completion of the required training will result in the person being able to make a formal application for authorisation under the <a href="http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_193_homepage.html">Conservation &amp; Land Management Act (CALM)</a> 1984, Swan and Canning Rivers Management Act 2006 and any other associated legislation through an application form which can be obtained from the Intranet or the <a href="mailto:regulatory.training@dpaw.wa.gov.au">Regulatory Training Coordinator</a>.</p>
<p>
In order for an Authorised Officer to retain their authority, they must participate and show competency in annual refresher training. Please contact Kharis Johnston - <a href="mailto:regulatory.training@dpaw.wa.gov.au">Regulatory Training Coordinator</a> for further information.<br /></p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
<h4 style="text-align:center;">Authorised Officer refresher to be held between 10th August (8:00 am) - 14th August (4:30 pm) 2015.</h4></div><p></p>";